window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The vows are just the beginning…</b></p> <p>For Natalie, being the wife to the most sought-after rock star on the planet has its privileges, but in the last year, she's been put through the wringer as far as the pitfalls.</p> <p>When Easton summons her to Mexico for a second-anniversary honeymoon vacation in the very place that brought them back together, Natalie becomes filled with hope to close the space between them…along with a special request—a request that leads them into a day-long exploration of sorting through their past while trying to imagine the rest of their future together.</p> <p>They'll soon recognize that to keep what they have, they'll have to rediscover each other. With a little reminder from both their parents, they'll realize the fight to keep what they hold most sacred begins <i>after</i> I do.</p> <p><i>Bittersweet Melody </i>is a novella that must be listened to after finishing <i>Drive</i> and <i>Reverse</i>.</p>"; 
